import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import statsmodels.api as sm
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], errors='ignore')
    temperature_data = data['temperature']
    plt.hist(temperature_data, bins='auto', edgecolor='black')
    plt.xlabel('Temperature (°C)')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of hourly temperature in Seattle in 2010?')
    
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
        plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
chart.show()
```

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
import statsmodels.api as sm
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], errors='ignore')
    ax = data.boxplot(column='pressure')
    avg_pressure = data['pressure'].mean()
    plt.axhline(y=avg_pressure, color='r', linestyle='--', label=f'Average Pressure: {avg_pressure:.2f}')
    plt.legend()
    plt.title('What is the average hourly pressure in Seattle in 2010?', wrap=True)
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        ax.xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
```
